-- ADB Expects India's Economy to Expand 8.5%; Forecasts Inflation at 7.5%
-- B y   K a r t i k   G o y a l
-- 2010-09-28T04:59:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/adb-expects-india-s-economy-to-expand-8-5-forecasts-inflation-at-7-5-.html
India’s economy may expand 8.5
percent in the financial year that ends March 31, 2011, the
Asian Development Bank said in an e-mailed report today.  ADB expects the South Asian country’s annual average
inflation rate at 7.5 percent in the current financial year,
according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kartik Goyal in New Delhi at 
 kgoyal@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
